<h2>Arizona Winter School 2016: Analytic Methods in Arithmetic Geometry</h2>

<p>
    AWS 2016 will be held March 12-16, 2016 at the
    University of Arizona in Tucson, AZ.
</p>

<ul>
    <li>
        Registration will open December 15..
        <br>
        The deadline to apply for funding is <b>January 8, 2016</b>.
    </li>
    <li>
      Speakers:
      <ul>
        <li><b><a href="http://homepages.math.uic.edu/~cojocaru/">Alina Carmen Cojocaru<a></b>: Frobenius distributions in GL-extensions</li>
        <li><b><a href="http://webusers.imj-prg.fr/~harald.helfgott/anglais/index.html">Harald Andr&eacute;s Helfgott</a></b>: Growth and expansion in groups of Lie type</li>
        <li><b><a href="http://people.epfl.ch/philippe.michel">Philippe Michel</a></b>: Analytic number theory for Frobenius trace functions</li>
        <li><b><a href="https://math.mit.edu/~drew/">Andrew Sutherland</a></b>: Sato-Tate distributions</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
      Organizers: Alina Bucur and David Zureick-Brown (main program),
      with Bryden Cais, Mirela Ciperiani, and Romyar Sharifi.
    </li>
</ul>
